    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;The Ipsilon Flow Management Protocol (IFMP), is a protocol for allowing a node to instruct an adjacent node to attach a layer 2 label to a specified IP flow.  This document provides information for the Internet community.  This memo does not specify an Internet standard of any kind.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
